Detailed Description

Class for holding a PIN.

When packed into or from a packet UserPIN looks like this. The first TYPE and Total size in bytes and the last TYPE is read by someone else when read from a packet. {tabular}{lll} Pos & Size & Destription \ pos & 4 bytes & TYPE_PIN \ +4 & 2 bytes & Total size in bytes \ +6 & 4 bytes & TYPE_PIN \ +10 & 2 bytes & Total size in bytes \ +12 & 4 bytes & ID \ +16 & string & The PIN. +X & string & The comment. {tabular}
